  "prompt": "What is average cost per couple to travel Bhutan from AHMEDABAD?",
  "response": "The cost of traveling from Ahmedabad to Bhutan can vary greatly based on several factors, including the time of year, mode of transportation, type of accommodations, and the activities you choose to engage in. Here is a rough estimate for a mid-range trip for two people:\n\n1. **Flights**: Round-trip flights from Ahmedabad to Paro, Bhutan\u2019s only international airport, may range from INR 30,000 to INR 50,000 per person depending on the season and how far in advance the tickets are booked.\n\n2. **Bhutan Visa**: International tourists are required to pay the Sustainable Development Fee (SDF) of USD 200 per person per night. This fee includes visa, accommodation, meals, a tour guide, and internal transport. For a 7-day trip, this comes to around USD 1400 per person, approximately INR 1,15,000.\n\n3. **Accommodations**: If you choose accommodations outside the standard ones provided through the SDF, such as upscale or exclusive hotels, costs can be higher. Mid-range accommodations might add INR 5,000 to INR 10,000 per person for the whole trip.\n\n4. **Other Expenses**: You might also incur additional expenses for shopping, tips, extra activities, or dining outside the package. This can add another INR 10,000 to INR 20,000 for a couple.\n\nPutting this all together, a mid-range trip for a couple might cost approximately INR 3,50,000 to INR 4,50,000 for a week-long trip. Prices can be lower or higher depending on your specific preferences and choices.",
